content: विप्लुत {%<ab>p. p.</ab>%} {@--1@} Drifted about. {@--2@} Drowned, submerged, deluged, overflowed. {@--3@} Confounded, disturbed. {@--4@} Ravaged, devastated. {@--5@} Lost, disappeared. {@--6@} Disgraced, dishonoured. {@--7@} Ruined. {@--8@} Obscured, disfigured. {@--9@} Depraved, dissolute, profligate, guilty of lewdness. {@--10@} Contrary, reverse. {@--11@} Turning out false; नैते वाचं विप्लुतां व्याहरंति <ls>U. 4. 18.</ls>
